org.knime.core.node

Class DynamicNodeFactory<T extends NodeModel>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.knime.core.node.NodeFactory<T>
      • org.knime.core.node.DynamicNodeFactory<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the node model of the factory
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MissingNodeFactory, VirtualParallelizedChunkPortObjectInNodeFactory, VirtualParallelizedChunkPortObjectOutNodeFactory, VirtualSubNodeInputNodeFactory, VirtualSubNodeOutputNodeFactory

    public abstract class DynamicNodeFactory<T extends NodeModel>
extends NodeFactory<T>
    A node factory to create nodes dynamically. It essentially creates the node description (usually given in the XXXNodeFactory.xml) dynamically.
    Since:
    2.6
    Author:
    Dominik Morent, KNIME.com, Zurich, Switzerland, Martin Horn, University of Konstanz, Thorsten Meinl, KNIME.com, Zurich, Switzerland

      • addNodeDescription

        @Deprecated
protected void addNodeDescription(org.knime.node2012.KnimeNodeDocument doc)
        Deprecated. override createNodeDescription() instead
        Subclasses should add the node description elements. The KnimeNodeDocument reflects the structure given in http://www.knime.org/Node.dtd and allows one to create the node description document more easily (generated by XMLBeans (see http://xmlbeans.apache.org/)
        Parameters:
        doc - the document to add the description to

      • createNodeDescription

        protected NodeDescription createNodeDescription()
        Creates the description for this node. The default implementation reads the factory's XML file. Subclasses may override this method in order to create the description by other means. In case of dynamic nodes the procedure is roughly as follows:
        1. Create a KnimeNodeDocument in the desired version (preferably the latest, e.g. KnimeNodeDocument)
        2. Populate the document
        3. Use one of the node description proxies (e.g. NodeDescription28Proxy) in order to return the NodeDescription
        Overrides:
        createNodeDescription in class NodeFactory<T extends NodeModel>
        Returns:
        the node description

      • parseNodeDescriptionFromFile

        protected NodeDescription parseNodeDescriptionFromFile()
        Calls NodeFactory.createNodeDescription(), which parses the corresponding xml file named after this factory class (same package). If that fails it logs it to the NodeLogger and returns an empty NoDescriptionProxy.
        Returns:
        The result of that call.
        Since:
        2.10
